Currently, there is no alert text being displayed, which is quite long, and even system admins don't know what to do if systems have crashed. So, our

Instead, we should be designing features to work with different admission levels.

Firat has 'admin controls' in his profile settings. This means that the user is an admin, and we should display more relevant user controls than with non-admin users.

If the user is just a normal user, we can pop-up the 'Help' pop-up. However, there is an easier way to get to it than just a normal click, and Quick Collections by Yoda is the best way to get to the power users, as they will be curious and click the links.
